					Purple critters shoot when their flight timer (a value that increases by 1 every frame until the flight time value is reached), divided by a predetermined divident leaves a specific remainder. You can change all the values in the fields underneath but you'll have to do the calculations on your own. By default, the flight timer is 60, the divident is 30 and the remainder needed is 6, so the critter shoots twice, at timer values of 6 and 36.
				</field>
